The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) in Benue State has declared PDP’s Chris Adaji, winner of Ohimini state constituency supplementary election. Adaji polled 6742 votes to defeat his closest rival, the APC’s Musa Alechenu who scored 6341 votes. Our correspondent reports that the result was declared by the returning officer, Prof. Nichodemus Abulu, at the INEC office in Idekpa, headquarters of Ohimini Local Government Area on Saturday night.  PDP wins Benue's supplementary election INEC fixes Saturday for election in Benue constituency 5 fake voters arrested in Benue's supplementary election